text: On September 2nd 2007, I uploaded the first theme in the list, Wild Arms' Town theme. I never thought the list would grow so much and especially that I would still be doing this 10 years later. Honestly, saying it's been 10 years boggles my mind. That's my whole 20s right there! Not having handicapped myself with a complex set of rules for this channel is the ingredient of its longevity. The fact that the 2007-2017 lapse feels absolutely shorter than 1997-2007 proves to me how much time passes by faster as we grow older. I started this channel because I was frustrated at the lack of video game music on YouTube, which was rapidly growing as a platform; even the biggest classics couldn't be found. I'm happy to see the VGM community so much stronger now, even if I still feel like gaming companies or even the press are still underestimating the importance of good and memorable music in video games to enhance the experience. Thank you everyone for the support!
